translated: Hovmantorp, Kronoborg. 1 child with Anna Charlotta Johansson: Gun-Britt, born in 1936. Completed elementary school teacher training in Växjö in 1912, graduated from high school in 1916, and received a Bachelor of Arts degree in Gothenburg in 1919. Traveled to England and Germany. Appointed as an elementary school teacher in Ryssby from 1913-1916, in Gothenburg from 1916-1930, as assistant principal in Gothenburg from 1926-1930, and as an elementary school inspector in Halmstad from 1930. Was appointed by the Ministry of Justice as an expert in the United Care Committee in 1941, assisting the chief expert in investigating the education of mentally disabled children. Served as chairman of the Child Welfare Board and the School Board of Halmstad and Halmstad School Inspectorate. Wrote a Swedish dictionary (27, 17th edition in 47) and articles on pedagogical matters in newspapers and journals.
